article.headline: New Orleans 86, Idaho State 72
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Johnell Smith scored 16 of his 27 points in the first half as New Orleans defeated Idaho State 86-72 Friday in the first game at the round-robin Adidas Festival. Idaho State (3-6) closed a 38-31 halftime deficit to 44-40 three minutes into the second half. New Orleans (4-2) called a timeout and responded with a 7-2 run to take control of the game. The Bengals got no closer than five points the rest of the way as New Orleans held them to a four-minute field goal drought midway through the second half. Victor Brown added a season high 18 points and 11 rebounds off the bench and Kyle Buggs scored 11 for New Orleans. Scott Henry scored 19 points and Jeff Gardner had 18 to lead the Bengals. After Idaho State cut New Orleans' lead to 20-18 in the first half, Smith scored all 11 of his team's points in an 11-3 run midway through the first half.
